sets version priority\n  - Calls AddToScheme for internal, v1, v1beta1, and v1alpha1\n  - Sets priority: v1 > v1beta1 > v1alpha1\n\n- **Version Registers**:\n  - `pkg/apis/networking/v1/register.go`: Registers v1 defaulting functions\n  - `pkg/apis/networking/v1beta1/register.go`: Registers v1beta1 defaulting functions\n\n### 8. Conversion Testing\n\n- **Conversion Tests** (`pkg/apis/networking/v1beta1/conversion_test.go`): TestIngressBackendConversion() validates:\n  - service-port-number conversion\n  - service-named-port conversion\n  - empty-service-name edge cases\n  - Bidirectional conversion (v1beta1 ↔ internal)\n\n### 9. Fuzzing Support\n\n- **Fuzzer** (`pkg/apis/networking/fuzzer/fuzzer.go`): Includes pathType fuzzing with all three valid values\n\n### Key Migration Points:\n\n1. **pathType became required**: Must be specified in v1, automatically defaults to ImplementationSpecific in v1beta1\n2. **Backend API changed**: v1beta1 uses ServiceName/ServicePort; v1 uses Service object with Name and Port\n3. **v1 is the storage version**: Objects are stored as v1 in etcd; v1beta1 requests are converted on read/write\n4. **Backward compatibility maintained**: Conversion functions ensure v1beta1 clients can still interact with the API\n5. **Validation enforced**: v1 validation requires pathType, while v1beta1 is permissive (defaulting applies)\n"
